# {{project}} — Claude Code operating manual

This file is loaded into every Claude Code session in this repo. It defines how
agents behave here. Treat it as binding.

## What this repo is
A full-Rust vertical slice: shared pure domain (`{{crate_prefix}}-core`), shared
Dioxus UI (`{{crate_prefix}}-ui`), a web/WASM target (`{{crate_prefix}}-web`), an
optional native mobile target (`{{crate_prefix}}-mobile`), and a Vercel serverless
function (`api/{{fn_name}}.rs`) backed by `{{crate_prefix}}-server`. The product
will change; the architecture and quality bar will not.

## Golden rules (non-negotiable)
1. **`{{crate_prefix}}-core` is sacred.** No UI, no I/O, no platform crates, no
   `unwrap()`/`expect()`/`panic!()` in non-test code. Errors are typed enums via
   `thiserror`.
2. **Every change ships with tests.** New logic in `core`/`server` requires unit
   tests; invariant-style logic gets a `proptest`. No test, no merge.
3. **CI is the gate.** `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo clippy -D warnings`, and
   `cargo test --workspace` must pass. Never weaken the gate to make a PR green.
4. **Dependency direction is one-way.** `core <- ui <- {web, mobile}`,
   `server -> core`. Never add a reverse edge.
5. **Small vertical slices.** Each PR is one thin, end-to-end, reviewable change.

## Workflow
- Branch from `main`. Open a PR. Let the `reviewer` and `security-auditor` agents
  run before requesting human review.
- Conventional commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `test:`, `docs:`, `build:`, `chore:`).
- Keep diffs surgical. If a change balloons, stop and split it.

## Commands you can run
- `cargo xtask ci` — the full local gate (fmt + clippy + test + wasm build)
- `cargo test --workspace` — full test suite
- `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` — lint gate
- `cargo fmt --all` — format
- `cargo xtask serve` (`dx serve`) — run the web app locally

## Deploy (prebuilt; see knowledge/05)
- From the repo root: `vercel build --prod --yes && vercel deploy --prebuilt --prod --yes`
- Vercel can't run `dx`, so deploys are prebuilt; the function cross-compiles via
  `cargo-zigbuild` + `zig`. Never weaken the gate to ship.

